snippet.textDisplay:
It sounds just like what it is: a crap Eurovision entry. All songs for Eurovision are crap, they just come in a sliding scale of crappiness. Some score higher on the crap level than others, but ffs people, get a grip - it’s Eurovision not a world changing event. There are a lot of facts to consider:
The fact that The UK’s entries are absolutely awful 99% of the time should come as no surprise. Even this entry (which is only marginally better than most) is hardly anything to write home about - it’s just another rubbish, unimaginative song that’s annoyingly repetitive.
The fact that we’re leaving the EU (because of Brexit) should’ve given enough material for song writers everywhere to be able to produce something better, more profound than THIS?!
And, a small but important point ....The UK is leaving the EU and as a result should disqualify it from being a participating country in Eurovision. So why is the UK still allowed to take part?

Of course, now what’ll happen now is that whenever we lose the Eurovision from this point on, nationalists will cry and lament that we only lost because the UK is being punished and is the victim of discrimination because of Brexit.
Brexit will only benefit a tiny majority in the UK whereas most of us will suffer because of it (yes, suffer) Despite this glaring injustice we’re ALL going to be made to suffer by having to listen to yet another cheesy Eurovision monstrosity played to its death on BBC radio 2.
